Thanks so much.  Thats exactly the kind of response I was hoping for.  I am hoping that it wasnt a post that would step on toes, and would like to re-state in this post as well that I am not looking to nerf Mages or steal any thing from them.<br>
<br>
I would love to know more about the nature of the different Mage pets.  DPS parses n stuff, maybe the Earth elemental scale is not such a bad idea.<br>
<br>
Also, the proc thing is kind of a mystery to us unfortunately.  You don't see the numbers saying when it hits, or when it gets resisted, or how much it hits for.  I think we would all feel more comfortable w/ some numbers to back up the damage.  I would agree that it has potential, especially if they made them resisted off of the different resists.  Would make sense to use Spirit of Vermin against a disease weak mob, instead of just scaling damage, make them each unique.  I would gladly take a proc that hits for 102 often over one that hits for 142 rarely.  I think most beastlords would.  As it is, eqcaster says they are all resisted w/ MR.<br>
<br>
Anyhow, I am still more than eager to hear from other Mage's regarding their pets and the tank v. melee.  I guess I am just coming in w/ the perspective that most Beastlords would expect.  Mages nuke for the majority of their DPS.  It sounds like that is not the case, and kind of steals the thunder from the argument that they dont need a high damaging pet.  Thansk for reading. (c:  And thanks for staying civil. <p><i>Please just look at the Sig for its beauty, I am really a lvl 57 Animist w/ Epic.</i><br><img src="http://www.ichuu.com/Tomonari/pics/yiktikiubersig.gif" usemap=#yik border=0><map name=yik><area href="http://www.ichuu.com/Tomonari/" coords="102,135, 248,195"><area href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=224581" coords="167,2, 324,32" target="_blank"><br></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#FF9933>- </font><a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/beqbeastlord>EQbeastlord</a><font color=#FF9933> - </font><a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1>The Den</a> <font color=#FF9933> - </font><a href="http://www.eqbeastlord.com">Beastlord home page</a><font color=#FF9933> - </font> </div>

